Vaping THC may be behind many of the serious lung diseases that have been tied to e-cigarette use––raising concerns about an increasingly popular way of consuming marijuana, which many consumers view as a relatively safe habit.
But a growing number of illnesses apparently tied to vaping THC may change some users’ minds—and remove the health halo that often surrounds vaping.
Cooper says a handful of studies on vaping cannabis have suggested that using e-cigarettes is less harmful to the lungs than smoking marijuana.
Perhaps in part because of that belief, vaping marijuana has grown increasingly popular.
And it’s not just legal users who are vaping marijuana: About 13% of high school seniors said they had in a federal survey released in December 2018.